<div class="container">

    <p class="">
        With campuses in Bloemfontein and Welkom, the Central University of Technology (CUT) is a well-known higher education establishment in South Africa. 
        
        <br /> <br/>
        It was founded in 1981 and provides a range of degrees in subjects like management sciences, humanities, and STEM. CUT, which has more than 21,000 students, strives to be a preeminent technological university in Africa with a focus on innovation and social impact. 
        Research and innovation are given priority, especially when it comes to additive manufacturing for use in the medical field. 
        
        <br />
        CUT seeks to address issues of national and regional development while promoting global engagement through collaborations and internationalization initiatives. 
        By 2030, CUT, which is dedicated to academic excellence and principles like ethics and Ubuntu, hopes to use innovation to shape the future.
    </p>
    
